---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Ball for Bloomfield">
    <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="wrap"><h1>Privacy Policy</h1></div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="wrap narrow">
            <p><em>Effective: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</em></p>

            <p>Ball for Bloomfield respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it.</p>

            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Donations:</strong> If you contribute, Iowa law requires us to collect and report your <strong>name</strong>, <strong
                        >address</strong
                    >, and the <strong>amount</strong> of your contribution to the Iowa Ethics and Campaign Disclosure Board (IECDB).
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Payment Information:</strong> Contributions are processed securely by Stripe. Ball for Bloomfield does not receive or store payment card
                    or bank information. See <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy">Stripe’s Privacy Policy</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Sign Requests:</strong> If you request a yard sign, we collect your <strong>name</strong>, <strong>address</strong>, <strong
                        >phone</strong
                    >, and <strong>email</strong> to verify and fulfill your request and to contact you about campaign-related information.
                </li>
                <li><strong>General Contact:</strong> If you reach out, we may collect your name and email to respond.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To process and report campaign contributions as required by law;</li>
                <li>To fulfill yard sign requests and contact supporters about campaign activities;</li>
                <li>To comply with state and federal campaign finance laws.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Text Messages</h2>
            <p>
                Any text messages you may receive will come directly from the candidate’s personal phone, not from an automated system. If you reply “STOP” or
                otherwise ask not to be contacted, we will manually honor your request and remove your number from future texts. You will not receive an
                automated confirmation when opting out.
            </p>

            <h2>Sharing of Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Required donor information (name, address, amount contributed) will be reported to the IECDB and may be publicly available.</li>
                <li>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Security</h2>
            <p>We take reasonable steps to protect the information you provide. Contributions are processed via Stripe’s secure platform.</p>

            <h2>Your Choices</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>You may opt out of campaign-related emails or texts by contacting us directly.</li>
                <li>You may request deletion of voluntary information (subject to campaign finance reporting requirements).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:chris@ballforbloomfield.com">chris@ballforbloomfield.com</a></p>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
